enumerations.name: DiagnosticOccurrenceCounterProcessingEnum
enumerations.note: The occurrence counter triggering types. Aggregated by DiagnosticCommonProps.occurrenceCounterProcessing

literals.name: confirmedDtcBit
literals.description:
The occurrence counter is incremented when TestFailed bit transitions from 0 to 1 if the fault confirmation was successful (ConfirmedDTC bit is already set).
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

literals.name: testFailedBit
literals.description:
The occurrence counter is incremented when TestFailed bit transitions from 0 to 1 (and the fault confirmation is not considered).
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

enumerations.name: DiagnosticEventCombinationBehaviorEnum
enumerations.note: Select type of Event Combination support Aggregated by DiagnosticCommonProps.typeOfEventCombinationSupported

literals.name: eventCombination
literals.description:
Event combination on retrieval is used to combine events. For each event an individual event memory OnRetrieval entry is created, while reporting the data via UDS, the data is combined.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=1

literals.name: eventCombination
literals.description: Event combination on storage is used to combine events. Only one memory entry exists for each

literals.name: OnStorage
literals.description:
DTC which is also reported via UDS.
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0

enumerations.name: DiagnosticEventCombinationReportingBehaviorEnum
enumerations.note: Select reporting format of events. Applicable only for Event Combination on Retrieval. Aggregated by DiagnosticCommonProps.eventCombinationReportingBehavior

literals.name: reportingInChronlogicalOrder
literals.description:
The reporting order for event combination on retrieval is the chronological storage order of the events
Tags: atp.EnumerationLiteralIndex=0
